WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.120
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:21.709 --> 00:00:22.544
Sis?

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:29.717
Dad…

00:00:34.889 --> 00:00:36.432
killed someone.

00:00:45.817 --> 00:00:47.110
I said Dad…

00:00:52.282 --> 00:00:53.992
killed someone.

00:00:55.910 --> 00:00:58.913
<i>But that's just your imagination.</i>

00:00:59.622 --> 00:01:00.957
It's not my imagination.

00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:02.876
I'm putting the pieces together.

00:01:04.752 --> 00:01:07.922
Then did you really see
the book all torn up?

00:01:08.006 --> 00:01:11.384
Yes. I happened to see it
when I went into Se-yun's room.

00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:13.845
His trash can was full of torn pages.

00:01:20.226 --> 00:01:21.144
No.

00:01:22.812 --> 00:01:24.189
Start over from the beginning.

00:01:27.358 --> 00:01:29.319
It's too early to conclude it's Se-yun.

00:01:31.738 --> 00:01:33.406
Nothing is certain yet.

00:01:37.035 --> 00:01:38.119
But

00:01:39.454 --> 00:01:40.914
Se-yun's been acting

00:01:42.332 --> 00:01:43.333
a bit strange lately.

00:01:48.463 --> 00:01:50.423
Strange? In what way?

00:01:53.676 --> 00:01:56.971
<i>He rarely comes out of his room</i>
<i>after he gets back from school.</i>

00:02:03.519 --> 00:02:04.646
Dinner's ready.

00:02:05.939 --> 00:02:06.856
I kept calling you.

00:02:13.029 --> 00:02:14.447
We should code after dinner.

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:17.450
Fuck that! Just leave me alone, will you?

00:02:20.536 --> 00:02:24.707
I don't give a crap about coding anymore,
so don't come in here again.

00:02:41.975 --> 00:02:43.685
<i>I've never seen him like that before.</i>

00:02:49.983 --> 00:02:50.817
Hey.

00:02:50.900 --> 00:02:52.360
Why are you alone?

00:02:53.361 --> 00:02:54.237
What about Yun?

00:02:55.196 --> 00:02:56.531
He says he's not hungry.

00:02:57.282 --> 00:02:58.283
Again?

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:02.161
He said the same yesterday.

00:03:03.663 --> 00:03:06.666
And he barely ate breakfast this morning
before he left for school.

00:03:07.333 --> 00:03:10.878
What's gotten into him lately?
Is something up with him?

00:03:14.299 --> 00:03:15.216
I'm not sure…

00:03:15.758 --> 00:03:17.927
I think he's been feeling down

00:03:19.262 --> 00:03:20.596
since that day.

00:03:21.389 --> 00:03:23.349
Can't blame him. I have too.

00:03:24.058 --> 00:03:24.892
Little brat.

00:03:24.976 --> 00:03:28.896
That's no excuse to lock himself
in his room and refuse to eat.

00:03:29.647 --> 00:03:30.857
I'll go get him.

00:03:31.607 --> 00:03:33.484
Honey, leave him be.

00:03:33.985 --> 00:03:35.320
I'll talk to him later…

00:03:37.613 --> 00:03:38.865
Hey, Kim Se-yun!

00:03:39.949 --> 00:03:41.159
<i>But the strangest thing…</i>

00:03:41.242 --> 00:03:42.076
Kim Se-yun!

00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:43.745
<i>…is his relationship with Mr. Kim.</i>

00:03:49.167 --> 00:03:51.544
You really don't have an appetite, do you?

00:03:56.507 --> 00:04:01.262
If we had Min-hui's braised short ribs,
he'd eat a whole bowl of rice in no time.

00:04:04.182 --> 00:04:07.143
Why would you bring up a dead person?

00:04:09.145 --> 00:04:09.979
Oh yeah.

00:04:10.730 --> 00:04:11.981
You're right.

00:04:12.523 --> 00:04:14.233
Her name keeps slipping out.

00:04:16.069 --> 00:04:18.112
I'm sorry. Sorry.

00:04:18.196 --> 00:04:20.073
Eat. Eat up, everyone.

00:04:27.789 --> 00:04:30.792
Maybe it's because of the funeral.

00:04:32.460 --> 00:04:35.380
I think I keep bringing her up
because it's weighing on my mind.

00:04:37.924 --> 00:04:41.427
I mean, I just feel so sorry for Min-hui.

00:04:43.388 --> 00:04:45.264
She hasn't even had a funeral yet.

00:04:46.432 --> 00:04:48.768
I heard they did find her family.

00:04:49.394 --> 00:04:51.562
She has a father who remarried,

00:04:52.063 --> 00:04:53.773
but he couldn't care less.

00:04:54.273 --> 00:04:58.194
I heard her sister was the only
close blood relative she had,

00:04:58.277 --> 00:04:59.529
but even she

00:05:00.613 --> 00:05:03.950
died of an illness last year.

00:05:06.661 --> 00:05:07.620
So then

00:05:08.454 --> 00:05:10.206
what about her funeral?

00:05:11.124 --> 00:05:12.667
That's what I'm saying.

00:05:14.293 --> 00:05:18.172
If nothing comes up, I should discuss it
with the president of our church group.

00:05:18.756 --> 00:05:21.801
If that happens,
we'd have to raise some funds.

00:05:21.884 --> 00:05:24.011
No, don't ask the church volunteer group.

00:05:25.471 --> 00:05:26.305
No?

00:05:26.973 --> 00:05:27.807
Why not?

00:05:28.307 --> 00:05:29.517
Fundraising or whatever…

00:05:31.936 --> 00:05:35.606
would take too long. The funeral
should be held as soon as possible.

00:05:36.274 --> 00:05:38.985
People might talk.

00:05:40.528 --> 00:05:42.697
That would be disrespectful
to the deceased.

00:05:43.865 --> 00:05:46.534
If money's the issue,
we can take care of it.

00:05:47.535 --> 00:05:48.536
I'll pay for it.

00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:50.788
-You will?
-Yeah.

00:05:51.831 --> 00:05:52.748
Of course.

00:05:52.832 --> 00:05:55.793
She <i>did </i>work in our home for a while.

00:05:55.877 --> 00:05:58.379
We should take care of her to the end.

00:05:58.880 --> 00:06:00.506
It's the least we could do.

00:06:03.134 --> 00:06:04.177
Oh, honey.

00:06:04.802 --> 00:06:06.012
You really are so--

00:06:06.095 --> 00:06:07.221
Thanks for the meal.

00:06:10.266 --> 00:06:11.392
Thanks for the meal.

00:06:17.899 --> 00:06:19.275
Repulsive bastard!

00:06:19.775 --> 00:06:20.985
That son of a bitch.

00:06:21.611 --> 00:06:22.445
Sorry?

00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:30.077
Se-yun.

00:06:31.329 --> 00:06:32.788
He seems completely fine

00:06:33.414 --> 00:06:35.625
whenever I see him at school.

00:06:35.708 --> 00:06:39.295
And his assignments are normal.
He always writes about trivial stuff.

00:06:39.378 --> 00:06:40.755
Yes, that's right.

00:06:40.838 --> 00:06:44.217
He's like that at home
but acts like nothing's wrong at school.

00:06:44.717 --> 00:06:46.344
Even plays ball with his friends.

00:06:49.472 --> 00:06:50.473
Kang.

00:06:51.307 --> 00:06:52.642
Time to revisit the hotel.

00:06:53.684 --> 00:06:55.269
-The hotel?
-Yeah.

00:06:56.062 --> 00:06:58.314
Always look before you leap, as they say.

00:06:59.148 --> 00:07:01.609
It's crucial to get
the facts straight first.

00:07:06.155 --> 00:07:08.199
It's time for our class. We should go.

00:07:08.282 --> 00:07:09.116
-Already?
-Hurry!

00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:10.701
-See you.
-Yeah.

00:07:35.977 --> 00:07:37.395
Was it really you?

00:07:39.647 --> 00:07:41.232
Se-yun.

00:07:43.985 --> 00:07:45.861
I hope it really was you.

00:07:54.662 --> 00:07:56.581
Kim Su-hun, you bastard.

00:07:57.456 --> 00:07:58.833
What the hell

00:08:00.293 --> 00:08:02.420
did your son find out about you?

00:08:18.894 --> 00:08:20.396
I was right, Mr. Heo.

00:08:20.896 --> 00:08:21.897
About Se-yun.

00:08:29.447 --> 00:08:30.448
I see.

00:08:31.991 --> 00:08:34.285
So it was him after all.

00:08:36.245 --> 00:08:38.914
I only managed to get this
by begging Jae-sik for it.

00:08:41.667 --> 00:08:42.585
We got it!

00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:44.962
We got it.

00:08:46.631 --> 00:08:47.840
So now,

00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:52.011
we just need to find out
what Kim Se-yun knows.

00:08:57.266 --> 00:08:58.392
Hey.

00:08:59.352 --> 00:09:00.561
Why the long face?

00:09:01.562 --> 00:09:02.396
Sorry?

00:09:03.648 --> 00:09:05.274
What do you…

00:09:06.901 --> 00:09:08.986
Why do you look like you just ate shit?

00:09:12.531 --> 00:09:13.824
Well, it's just…

00:09:14.909 --> 00:09:16.160
Just what?

00:09:17.536 --> 00:09:18.954
You got something else to say?

00:09:19.955 --> 00:09:20.998
If so, go ahead.

00:09:25.670 --> 00:09:28.881
My mind is all over the place
thinking about Se-yun.

00:09:33.844 --> 00:09:35.221
Until recently,

00:09:36.222 --> 00:09:39.684
it felt pretty satisfying to find out
that Mr. Kim was a bad person.

00:09:40.768 --> 00:09:41.852
Do you know why?

00:09:44.271 --> 00:09:46.148
Se-yun was kind of annoying.

00:09:47.274 --> 00:09:50.361
He seemed to have the perfect life
and everything he could ever want.

00:09:54.031 --> 00:09:55.658
But seeing him these days…

00:09:59.829 --> 00:10:01.455
I guess it really does hurt

00:10:02.665 --> 00:10:04.208
to watch a friend suffer.

00:10:18.389 --> 00:10:19.849
Yeah, exactly.

00:10:20.725 --> 00:10:22.435
That's why we're helping Se-yun.

00:10:24.687 --> 00:10:25.521
Sorry?

00:10:26.689 --> 00:10:27.857
Don't you get it?

00:10:28.649 --> 00:10:32.153
If we find out what Kim Se-yun knows,

00:10:33.154 --> 00:10:37.450
we might be able to help him.
Ever heard of thinking outside the box?

00:10:41.704 --> 00:10:44.206
Besides,
that's the thing about friendship.

00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:47.376
Covering up the truth
isn't always the best solution.

00:10:47.877 --> 00:10:51.005
Sometimes, uncovering the truth

00:10:51.505 --> 00:10:55.301
and making your friend face it
can be the best thing for them.

00:10:59.305 --> 00:11:00.264
Are we good now?

00:11:01.140 --> 00:11:02.516
From now on,

00:11:03.309 --> 00:11:04.935
whenever you're conflicted,

00:11:06.604 --> 00:11:09.482
remind yourself
that we're helping your friend.

00:11:10.858 --> 00:11:11.776
Okay.

00:11:14.653 --> 00:11:15.863
By the way, Mr. Heo,

00:11:16.947 --> 00:11:18.115
I have some news.

00:11:19.408 --> 00:11:20.326
News?

00:11:20.409 --> 00:11:24.622
Se-yun's sister, Jeong-hu,
is coming home on Sunday.

00:11:25.539 --> 00:11:26.957
It's Mr. Kim's birthday.

00:11:29.001 --> 00:11:30.461
Kim Su-hun's birthday?

00:11:31.045 --> 00:11:35.508
Se-yun is really close to his sister.
They seem to stay in touch a lot too.

00:11:38.093 --> 00:11:39.094
Is that right?

00:11:41.639 --> 00:11:44.016
Then listen to every single word

00:11:44.517 --> 00:11:45.601
those two exchange

00:11:46.101 --> 00:11:47.645
when they're alone.

00:11:48.312 --> 00:11:50.356
Something <i>will </i>come up
in their conversations.

00:11:51.232 --> 00:11:52.358
That is this week's

00:11:53.275 --> 00:11:54.777
investigative assignment.

00:12:06.997 --> 00:12:07.832
Here.

00:12:12.127 --> 00:12:13.337
Even

00:12:13.963 --> 00:12:15.506
your autograph is cool.

00:12:16.131 --> 00:12:16.966
Like your novel.

00:12:18.634 --> 00:12:19.802
The honor is mine.

00:12:20.302 --> 00:12:23.764
Se-yun, on the other hand,
has zero interest in what I write.

00:12:26.267 --> 00:12:27.101
Here.

00:12:28.894 --> 00:12:30.145
Where's Dad?

00:12:30.688 --> 00:12:32.273
The man of the hour?

00:12:32.356 --> 00:12:33.524
Dad?

00:12:34.984 --> 00:12:38.362
Your dad went to Min-hui's funeral.

00:12:38.863 --> 00:12:43.033
He'll be back this evening
after running some errands.

00:12:43.534 --> 00:12:44.869
Her funeral?

00:12:45.578 --> 00:12:46.412
Of all days…

00:12:48.163 --> 00:12:50.082
So it's happening after all.

00:12:50.165 --> 00:12:51.709
It's a relief

00:12:52.209 --> 00:12:54.545
that they can finally hold the funeral.

00:12:55.421 --> 00:12:58.841
I wanted to go with him,
but your dad told me to stay home--

00:12:58.924 --> 00:13:00.301
Why would you go?

00:13:02.511 --> 00:13:05.431
What do you mean, why?
I'd have reason to attend, wouldn't I?

00:13:07.266 --> 00:13:08.142
I just mean,

00:13:09.435 --> 00:13:13.105
I haven't visited in a while.
If both of you weren't here, it'd be…

00:13:15.357 --> 00:13:16.275
There he is.

00:13:17.192 --> 00:13:18.444
Did you just wake up?

00:13:19.486 --> 00:13:20.529
You're here.

00:13:21.822 --> 00:13:25.075
All done sleeping now, sleepyhead?

00:13:26.076 --> 00:13:28.287
Still, you managed to get him downstairs.

00:13:28.787 --> 00:13:30.414
What? What do you mean?

00:13:31.707 --> 00:13:34.126
This one's been holed up
in his room lately,

00:13:34.209 --> 00:13:35.794
gaming all day and night.

00:13:35.878 --> 00:13:37.421
You should give him a talking-to.

00:13:38.923 --> 00:13:43.385
Yun's always listened to his sister,
ever since he was a kid.

00:13:44.094 --> 00:13:45.721
He was always her shadow.

00:13:48.557 --> 00:13:50.351
Then I should give him a talking-to.

00:13:50.434 --> 00:13:53.938
Hey, you little shit.
Come with me. You're dead meat.

00:13:54.021 --> 00:13:55.481
I won't go easy on you.

00:13:55.564 --> 00:13:58.108
-I told you to be good, didn't I?
-Excuse me?

00:13:59.109 --> 00:14:01.654
-Hey, you punk.
-I'm not a little kid anymore.

00:14:01.737 --> 00:14:02.571
Hey.

00:14:02.655 --> 00:14:05.407
All right, then.
Take it easy until your dad gets home.

00:14:05.491 --> 00:14:07.409
-Don't move.
-I have a lot of work to do.

00:14:07.493 --> 00:14:08.994
Let go. Three, two…

00:14:33.352 --> 00:14:34.770
How shameless.

00:14:35.437 --> 00:14:38.357
He went to that woman's funeral
on a family day?

00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:45.656
He must feel a little guilty for cheating,
seeing how he wouldn't let Mom go.

00:14:45.739 --> 00:14:48.617
<i>As I expected, Jeong-hu knows too.</i>

00:14:48.701 --> 00:14:50.911
But how can Mom be so blind
to all of this?

00:14:51.412 --> 00:14:53.247
And she actually wanted to go?

00:14:53.330 --> 00:14:55.290
Seriously, it drives me crazy.

00:14:56.625 --> 00:14:57.626
No.

00:14:59.086 --> 00:15:00.379
It's good Mom doesn't know.

00:15:03.132 --> 00:15:05.050
If I'm honest,

00:15:05.551 --> 00:15:07.594
I think Mom should know too.

00:15:07.678 --> 00:15:10.597
How long has Dad been womanizing
in the name of art?

00:15:14.393 --> 00:15:16.228
Should we just drop the bomb today?

00:15:16.311 --> 00:15:19.398
-To hell with his birthday.
-No, you can't!

00:15:24.611 --> 00:15:28.032
Someone as sensitive as Mom
wouldn't be able to handle it.

00:15:29.950 --> 00:15:31.410
Don't you remember?

00:15:31.910 --> 00:15:35.414
Years ago, when Mom was depressed,
and she took some pills

00:15:35.998 --> 00:15:37.666
to kill herself.

00:15:40.044 --> 00:15:42.337
Mom must think I don't know,
but I remember it all.

00:15:42.421 --> 00:15:43.964
But if she finds out about this…

00:15:46.717 --> 00:15:48.761
No. I'm going to protect Mom.

00:15:48.844 --> 00:15:51.221
Okay, I get it.

00:15:52.347 --> 00:15:54.933
That's why I'm keeping my mouth shut.

00:15:57.352 --> 00:16:00.647
But, fucking hell,
this one is a real shocker.

00:16:00.731 --> 00:16:02.524
She used to work in our home!

00:16:02.608 --> 00:16:04.234
He's a real piece of shit.

00:16:05.402 --> 00:16:07.529
And to top it all off, that accident…

00:16:10.741 --> 00:16:11.742
But

00:16:13.243 --> 00:16:14.286
Min-hui…

00:16:16.914 --> 00:16:18.499
didn't die from an accident.

00:16:20.501 --> 00:16:21.335
What?

00:16:22.294 --> 00:16:25.089
I couldn't bring myself
to tell you over the phone.

00:16:25.756 --> 00:16:27.800
Then tell me now.
What do you mean by that?

00:16:30.677 --> 00:16:31.970
Min-hui…

00:16:35.099 --> 00:16:36.683
Dad killed her.

00:16:38.811 --> 00:16:39.937
What did you say?

00:16:41.647 --> 00:16:42.898
Well, you see…

00:16:43.524 --> 00:16:44.566
Jeong-hu.

00:16:45.067 --> 00:16:45.901
Se-yun.

00:16:47.736 --> 00:16:48.570
Kim Jeong-hu.

00:16:49.905 --> 00:16:50.823
Kim Se-yun.

00:16:53.492 --> 00:16:56.078
Kang, where are the kids?

00:16:56.161 --> 00:16:57.704
Why aren't they answering?

00:16:58.622 --> 00:16:59.665
I don't know.

00:17:00.374 --> 00:17:01.458
I'm not really sure…

00:17:02.209 --> 00:17:05.295
Then could you come and take a look, Kang?

00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:07.214
Sorry?

00:17:24.148 --> 00:17:26.567
What do you think? Does it look okay?

00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:31.947
For some reason,
I wanted to make it myself this year.

00:17:32.447 --> 00:17:33.532
What do you think?

00:17:34.533 --> 00:17:36.243
Should I add more decorations?

00:17:36.326 --> 00:17:39.705
No, it's good. Much prettier
than the ones sold in stores.

00:17:40.330 --> 00:17:41.248
Really?

00:17:42.124 --> 00:17:43.083
You think so?

00:17:43.584 --> 00:17:44.710
Yes, really.

00:17:46.378 --> 00:17:47.588
I'll be going, then.

00:17:48.088 --> 00:17:49.089
What do you think

00:17:49.756 --> 00:17:52.259
I should write on top?

00:17:52.885 --> 00:17:55.262
Perhaps a unique birthday message?

00:18:00.184 --> 00:18:01.351
No way.

00:18:01.852 --> 00:18:03.854
No, you must have seen wrong.

00:18:05.355 --> 00:18:07.816
Sure, Dad's a bastard,
but he wouldn't do that.

00:18:07.900 --> 00:18:09.526
No, I saw everything--

00:18:09.610 --> 00:18:11.153
I said it can't be true!

00:18:13.655 --> 00:18:14.656
<i>Unfortunately,</i>

00:18:15.157 --> 00:18:18.911
<i>the important part of the conversation</i>
<i>was already over by the time I arrived.</i>

00:18:22.372 --> 00:18:23.999
What happened is

00:18:25.417 --> 00:18:27.586
you lost your mind from gaming too hard.

00:18:27.669 --> 00:18:28.921
A crazy hallucination.

00:18:29.004 --> 00:18:30.881
<i>-But I did learn…</i>
-Don't say that!

00:18:30.964 --> 00:18:32.299
<i>…one crucial fact.</i>

00:18:32.382 --> 00:18:33.508
I told you.

00:18:34.009 --> 00:18:37.346
I secretly tailed them
to the hospital after the accident.

00:19:00.702 --> 00:19:01.620
All right.

00:19:02.371 --> 00:19:04.623
Let's say, for argument's sake,
that it's true.

00:19:05.332 --> 00:19:06.959
In that case,

00:19:07.626 --> 00:19:10.337
this wouldn't just be a scandalous affair.

00:19:10.420 --> 00:19:11.505
It would mean…

00:19:13.757 --> 00:19:16.093
the reputation that Dad's built up,

00:19:17.010 --> 00:19:18.929
and the world I've just stepped into…

00:19:19.012 --> 00:19:21.515
It would all go up in flames.

00:19:22.015 --> 00:19:22.849
You get that?

00:19:23.642 --> 00:19:25.602
-Jeong-hu.
-You…

00:19:26.228 --> 00:19:27.896
Have you told anyone about this?

00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:29.314
Lee Kang.

00:19:29.982 --> 00:19:31.149
Did you tell him?

00:19:31.233 --> 00:19:33.902
Why would I tell anyone else?
I only told you.

00:19:37.990 --> 00:19:41.076
Okay, that's fine. That's fine, then.

00:19:42.202 --> 00:19:43.287
Jeong-hu.

00:19:43.370 --> 00:19:44.579
Okay, yeah.

00:19:44.663 --> 00:19:47.207
Then you just need to keep
your mouth shut. That's all.

00:19:47.708 --> 00:19:50.711
Thankfully, it seems like
the police overlooked it, too,

00:19:50.794 --> 00:19:52.379
so everything's fine.

00:20:00.679 --> 00:20:02.097
Jeong-hu, you're really…

00:20:11.189 --> 00:20:12.858
You weak-ass piece of shit.

00:20:13.942 --> 00:20:15.527
If you don't do as I say,

00:20:16.570 --> 00:20:18.196
I will kill you.

00:20:19.197 --> 00:20:20.574
I'll make you pay.

00:20:33.086 --> 00:20:34.171
<i>Se-yun</i>

00:20:34.671 --> 00:20:36.882
<i>shut himself up in his room again.</i>

00:20:39.134 --> 00:20:42.179
Yun, what are you doing? Come out here.

00:20:43.513 --> 00:20:44.973
Jeong-hu's leaving.

00:20:48.143 --> 00:20:52.064
<i>He didn't even come out</i>
<i>to see Jeong-hu off.</i>

00:20:56.651 --> 00:20:58.153
Are you okay, Mr. Heo?

00:21:04.326 --> 00:21:05.744
Well,

00:21:05.827 --> 00:21:08.205
I just heard so many shocking things.

00:21:10.332 --> 00:21:12.334
I don't even know where to start.

00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:14.795
I know, right?

00:21:15.337 --> 00:21:17.547
I was shocked at every turn too.

00:21:18.965 --> 00:21:21.301
I had no idea they had so many secrets.

00:21:22.761 --> 00:21:24.846
I see that house completely differently

00:21:25.347 --> 00:21:26.765
from my first visit now.

00:21:27.349 --> 00:21:28.350
In any case…

00:21:30.644 --> 00:21:32.145
we're back to square one.

00:21:33.855 --> 00:21:36.066
You didn't hear anything definitive.

00:21:36.566 --> 00:21:38.235
But one thing's for certain.

00:21:38.318 --> 00:21:42.155
Se-yun knows something.
And he was at the hotel that day--

00:21:42.239 --> 00:21:44.157
That's right. That's it.

00:21:45.283 --> 00:21:48.036
He was definitely
at the scene of the accident.

00:21:48.537 --> 00:21:50.956
And he tailed them to the hospital
and saw something.

00:21:51.706 --> 00:21:52.624
Yes.

00:21:53.583 --> 00:21:55.544
That's the most surprising part.

00:21:58.296 --> 00:22:00.132
How did Se-yun know to go to the hotel,

00:22:01.341 --> 00:22:03.301
and what did he see at the hospital?

00:22:03.802 --> 00:22:04.886
But

00:22:05.720 --> 00:22:08.056
the kicker is that his own sister

00:22:08.640 --> 00:22:10.642
muzzled him.

00:22:12.477 --> 00:22:16.982
So the key now is getting Se-yun to talk.

00:22:17.482 --> 00:22:20.402
Speaking of which,
we need to take drastic measures.

00:22:21.695 --> 00:22:22.571
Drastic measures?

00:22:23.363 --> 00:22:26.199
I think we'll have to get
Mrs. Ahn involved.

00:22:28.493 --> 00:22:29.578
-Eun-joo?
-Yes.

00:22:31.997 --> 00:22:33.248
"Eun-joo"?

00:22:34.499 --> 00:22:36.293
Do you know her personally too?

00:22:36.376 --> 00:22:37.794
That's not important.

00:22:39.045 --> 00:22:40.881
Get her involved? How?

00:22:40.964 --> 00:22:46.178
Well, Mrs. Ahn is the only one left,
since Jeong-hu is a lost cause.

00:22:46.678 --> 00:22:48.513
And there's no way he'll open up to me.

00:22:48.597 --> 00:22:52.100
So we give Mrs. Ahn a glimpse of the truth

00:22:52.184 --> 00:22:55.645
to make her question Se-yun herself.

00:22:56.146 --> 00:22:58.190
Right now, she knows nothing.

00:23:01.234 --> 00:23:03.278
Isn't that a good plan to find out more?

00:23:03.361 --> 00:23:04.488
No.

00:23:06.406 --> 00:23:07.240
Why not?

00:23:07.324 --> 00:23:09.201
Don't you remember what Se-yun said?

00:23:10.494 --> 00:23:12.037
He said his mom took pills

00:23:12.537 --> 00:23:14.414
and almost killed herself!

00:23:21.171 --> 00:23:24.216
You gotta pity the poor kid,
being so worried about his mom, right?

00:23:24.299 --> 00:23:25.592
Still,

00:23:27.052 --> 00:23:30.180
it's the only shot we've got
at finding out the truth.

00:23:35.477 --> 00:23:37.437
Now you're the one hesitating.

00:23:38.522 --> 00:23:39.606
Why is that?

00:23:40.482 --> 00:23:42.025
Is it because of Mrs. Ahn?

00:23:43.026 --> 00:23:44.402
Are you worried about her?

00:23:45.195 --> 00:23:47.531
-What's your relationship with her?
-We're nothing!

00:23:48.031 --> 00:23:50.742
We're just acquaintances
from my junior year in college!

00:23:51.910 --> 00:23:53.662
Satisfied? You punk.

00:24:01.461 --> 00:24:02.379
Anyway…

00:24:08.468 --> 00:24:11.846
we'll discuss this again at length later.

00:24:14.599 --> 00:24:15.850
Let's call it a day.

00:24:16.434 --> 00:24:18.645
I'm tired.
Make sure to write everything up

00:24:19.229 --> 00:24:21.439
and submit your assignment
as soon as possible.

00:24:38.873 --> 00:24:40.500
-Hey, what's up?
<i>-Hello, Professor.</i>

00:24:40.584 --> 00:24:43.670
<i>Are you aware that there's</i>
<i>an academic forum at 2:00 p.m. today?</i>

00:24:43.753 --> 00:24:45.589
<i>-The president asked.</i>
-Right.

00:24:45.672 --> 00:24:47.549
<i>Since you haven't submitted your paper.</i>

00:24:50.552 --> 00:24:52.095
Okay, I'll send it over now.

00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:56.182
I said I got it. 2:00 p.m.

00:25:04.190 --> 00:25:09.195
I was just passing by
and thought we could have lunch together.

00:25:10.447 --> 00:25:11.906
Okay, honey.

00:25:13.658 --> 00:25:16.453
Enjoy class. Okay.

00:25:17.037 --> 00:25:19.539
I'll see you at home. Bye.

00:26:49.713 --> 00:26:50.714
It's you.

00:26:52.006 --> 00:26:53.216
It's really you.

00:27:00.265 --> 00:27:01.516
Ahn Eun-joo.

00:27:02.851 --> 00:27:03.893
Eun-joo.

00:27:12.694 --> 00:27:14.904
TEACHING ASSISTANT KIM MI-SEO

00:29:24.284 --> 00:29:27.036
Honey, why did you come so early?

00:29:27.120 --> 00:29:28.788
Because I missed you, of course.

00:29:28.872 --> 00:29:30.081
You tease.

00:29:36.838 --> 00:29:38.381
Is it too cryptic?

00:29:38.464 --> 00:29:39.507
No, it's nice.

00:29:40.008 --> 00:29:41.301
There it is.

00:29:43.553 --> 00:29:44.888
-Right.
-What do you think?

00:29:45.972 --> 00:29:47.056
Yeah, it's nice.

00:29:47.557 --> 00:29:49.893
Seeing those kids eat is making me hungry.

00:29:51.895 --> 00:29:53.605
Is it too dark?

00:29:54.230 --> 00:29:55.106
No.

00:29:56.190 --> 00:29:57.317
What do you want to eat?

00:29:58.109 --> 00:29:59.652
-Are you hungry?
-Yeah.

00:29:59.736 --> 00:30:00.904
What should we eat?

00:30:03.156 --> 00:30:05.992
Should we have pasta? Or how about pizza?

00:30:06.492 --> 00:30:08.494
-Let's just order both.
-Okay.

00:30:08.995 --> 00:30:10.204
There's one up there too.

00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:17.814
Eun-joo.

00:31:18.439 --> 00:31:19.482
Eun-joo.

00:31:24.570 --> 00:31:27.365
What do I do now? Now what do I do?

00:31:27.448 --> 00:31:28.866
What should I do?

00:31:35.999 --> 00:31:37.250
What do I do now?

00:31:45.508 --> 00:31:46.551
What do I do?

00:31:54.809 --> 00:31:56.602
What are you muttering to yourself?

00:31:57.770 --> 00:31:59.522
You haven't even changed your clothes.

00:32:04.736 --> 00:32:06.112
How about a glass of wine?

00:32:15.079 --> 00:32:18.291
The couple I met for their final session
gave it to me today.

00:32:18.374 --> 00:32:20.209
They said they're doing much better.

00:32:23.212 --> 00:32:28.092
When they first came to see me,
they were in a really bad place.

00:32:30.428 --> 00:32:31.304
But…

00:32:33.181 --> 00:32:36.017
after just a few sessions,
things improved noticeably.

00:32:38.102 --> 00:32:41.481
It made me realize
how important it is to talk.

00:32:46.986 --> 00:32:49.238
Why were you lying down like that earlier?

00:32:50.406 --> 00:32:51.491
Did something happen?

00:32:52.408 --> 00:32:53.868
You don't look so good.

00:32:55.870 --> 00:32:57.288
I'm just a little tired.

00:33:03.002 --> 00:33:06.964
Have you stopped those literature lessons?
I liked how energetic they made you.

00:33:08.299 --> 00:33:11.385
I already told you.
I'm not doing them anymore.

00:33:19.018 --> 00:33:21.562
So you won't sleep in my room
anymore either?

00:33:24.482 --> 00:33:25.525
What is it…

00:33:27.401 --> 00:33:28.569
that you want to say?

00:33:37.161 --> 00:33:38.955
I want to apologize to you.

00:33:39.455 --> 00:33:41.124
I went too far that day.

00:33:45.837 --> 00:33:47.713
You know, the day we went to the movies.

00:33:48.965 --> 00:33:50.675
In the heat of the moment, I asked

00:33:51.759 --> 00:33:54.137
if you had an inferiority complex
toward Kim Su-hun.

00:33:56.055 --> 00:33:58.266
What I said kept bothering me.

00:33:59.600 --> 00:34:00.977
I know

00:34:02.395 --> 00:34:04.981
writers are sensitive
about that kind of thing.

00:34:07.191 --> 00:34:09.777
I know better than anybody…

00:34:11.404 --> 00:34:13.656
how much you struggled
when you couldn't write.

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:15.116
That's enough.

00:34:17.285 --> 00:34:18.828
Why bring that up again?

00:34:20.538 --> 00:34:22.665
I'm just apologizing

00:34:22.748 --> 00:34:25.168
for crossing a line that day.

00:34:42.185 --> 00:34:43.811
What? Who is it?

00:34:47.565 --> 00:34:48.441
Honey.

00:34:49.692 --> 00:34:50.651
Honey?

00:35:05.208 --> 00:35:07.835
Hey, what's this? What picture is this?

00:35:08.544 --> 00:35:10.630
<i>A letter. I took a picture of a letter.</i>

00:35:10.713 --> 00:35:13.257
<i>A strange letter arrived</i>
<i>at the house this afternoon.</i>

00:35:13.799 --> 00:35:14.634
A letter?

00:35:26.145 --> 00:35:27.313
What's this?

00:35:29.023 --> 00:35:30.608
There's no sender.

00:35:31.234 --> 00:35:32.526
Just your name.

00:35:32.610 --> 00:35:33.611
What?

00:35:35.071 --> 00:35:36.697
KIM SU-HUN

00:35:38.866 --> 00:35:39.867
Welcome home.

00:35:39.951 --> 00:35:40.910
Hey.

00:35:41.869 --> 00:35:43.079
Is Yun home too?

00:35:43.162 --> 00:35:45.665
Yes, he's been gaming
since he got home earlier.

00:35:49.627 --> 00:35:51.879
Then could you help put these away?

00:35:52.380 --> 00:35:54.090
I'm going to go and check in on Yun.

00:35:54.173 --> 00:35:55.883
Sure, go ahead. I'll put these away.

00:35:59.887 --> 00:36:00.721
Yun!

00:36:01.764 --> 00:36:03.266
Mom's home!

00:36:04.850 --> 00:36:07.687
We brought your favorite pizza
from Mangwon-dong!

00:36:11.190 --> 00:36:12.149
What is it?

00:36:13.109 --> 00:36:14.026
Nothing.

00:36:14.652 --> 00:36:16.862
Just fan mail. Nothing important.

00:36:19.865 --> 00:36:21.033
Fan mail?

00:36:22.285 --> 00:36:24.495
A handwritten letter, not an email?

00:36:25.621 --> 00:36:27.456
It happens from time to time.

00:36:27.999 --> 00:36:31.419
Older fans like
this sort of sentimentality.

00:36:37.717 --> 00:36:39.010
Damn it.

00:36:47.226 --> 00:36:48.769
<i>Mr. Kim was acting strange.</i>

00:36:49.437 --> 00:36:51.063
<i>Even his hands were shaking.</i>

00:40:31.367 --> 00:40:33.077
I HAVE THE HOSPITAL CCTV FOOTAGE

00:40:33.160 --> 00:40:35.496
10 PM TONIGHT
CENTRAL FOUNTAIN IN SEONGCHANG PARK

00:40:43.504 --> 00:40:44.838
Hospital CCTV footage?

00:40:46.799 --> 00:40:48.300
Does it really exist?

00:40:48.384 --> 00:40:51.095
<i>I don't know yet,</i>
<i>but that's what the letter said.</i>

00:40:51.178 --> 00:40:52.429
Right.

00:40:53.472 --> 00:40:56.475
If the footage really exists,
it would be the nail in the coffin.

00:40:57.893 --> 00:41:01.188
But who sent this letter?
Was it Kim Se-yun?

00:41:01.689 --> 00:41:04.191
<i>-He's our best bet at the moment.</i>
-Right.

00:41:05.025 --> 00:41:08.487
Kim Se-yun did mention
the hospital to his sister.

00:41:09.530 --> 00:41:10.906
<i>Yeah, there's that,</i>

00:41:11.615 --> 00:41:13.284
<i>but something else happened.</i>

00:41:14.535 --> 00:41:15.411
Something else?

00:41:15.494 --> 00:41:17.955
<i>Yes, during dinner tonight.</i>

00:41:26.255 --> 00:41:28.924
This place's pizza really is
the best way to lure Yun out.

00:41:29.008 --> 00:41:30.801
You were right, honey.

00:41:32.678 --> 00:41:33.512
What is it?

00:41:34.179 --> 00:41:35.848
What's on your mind, honey?

00:41:36.724 --> 00:41:37.558
Nothing.

00:41:38.225 --> 00:41:40.352
You're right.
This place has the best pizza.

00:41:45.107 --> 00:41:49.445
How about we go see a late-night movie
after this? It's been a while.

00:41:50.112 --> 00:41:51.322
A late-night movie?

00:41:51.405 --> 00:41:53.657
Or we could just go for a drive.

00:41:53.741 --> 00:41:55.409
Doesn't that sound wonderful?

00:41:55.492 --> 00:41:58.412
It'd be a waste to stay home
on a night like this.

00:41:59.038 --> 00:42:01.957
No, I can't. I have plans,
so I have to go out in a bit.

00:42:02.041 --> 00:42:04.877
Plans? What plans? All of a sudden?

00:42:04.960 --> 00:42:07.004
Yeah, suddenly.
Mr. Choi asked to meet, so…

00:42:08.047 --> 00:42:10.174
You three should go to a movie
or for a drive.

00:42:10.966 --> 00:42:14.136
Come on. It wouldn't be fun without you.

00:42:14.803 --> 00:42:16.096
I'll pass for today too.

00:42:16.597 --> 00:42:19.433
I'm meeting friends
from my department at 10:00 p.m.

00:42:20.142 --> 00:42:22.227
You too? All of a sudden?

00:42:22.311 --> 00:42:24.229
It's not exactly sudden.

00:42:25.689 --> 00:42:27.358
I've been waiting for it for ages.

00:42:36.825 --> 00:42:38.577
<i>Se-yun's eyes looked different.</i>

00:42:39.870 --> 00:42:41.330
<i>As though he'd made up his mind.</i>

00:42:42.748 --> 00:42:46.335
I'm heading to the place
mentioned in the letter now.

00:42:48.629 --> 00:42:49.630
Hey!

00:42:50.130 --> 00:42:53.759
You're heading there now?
You're moving without my orders?

00:42:54.259 --> 00:42:55.678
<i>You said</i>

00:42:56.178 --> 00:42:59.473
<i>that when I'm conflicted, I should</i>
<i>remind myself what all this is for.</i>

00:43:00.849 --> 00:43:01.767
What?

00:43:01.850 --> 00:43:04.061
<i>I'm going there to help my friend.</i>

00:43:07.690 --> 00:43:08.857
I see.

00:43:10.234 --> 00:43:12.403
<i>Se-yun's finally worked up the courage.</i>

00:43:12.903 --> 00:43:15.698
<i>If I witness that scene,</i>
<i>I'll be able to find something out.</i>

00:43:21.662 --> 00:43:23.831
Okay, I understand. Go ahead.

00:43:24.373 --> 00:43:28.627
And call me as soon as it's over, okay?

00:43:29.962 --> 00:43:31.130
And one more thing.

00:43:32.089 --> 00:43:35.259
You must not get caught.
You understand, don't you?

00:43:36.009 --> 00:43:36.969
Yes, I do.

00:43:38.178 --> 00:43:39.346
I'll call you.

00:44:10.627 --> 00:44:11.795
Honey.

00:44:15.424 --> 00:44:17.217
Why are you lying again?

00:44:17.760 --> 00:44:19.553
You said you stopped the lessons.

00:44:24.183 --> 00:44:26.435
And what was all that
weird stuff you said?

00:44:27.561 --> 00:44:29.521
What did you mean
about not getting caught?

00:44:30.647 --> 00:44:32.524
Eavesdropping again? How uncivilized.

00:44:34.693 --> 00:44:35.569
Uncivilized?

00:44:38.155 --> 00:44:39.698
If you're drunk, just go to bed.

00:44:40.741 --> 00:44:43.327
-Hey, Heo Mun-oh.
-Stop it!

00:44:43.410 --> 00:44:45.662
I said stop it, okay?

00:44:46.455 --> 00:44:48.415
I told you to keep your nose out.

00:44:48.957 --> 00:44:50.000
Do you have any idea

00:44:50.959 --> 00:44:52.544
how serious the situation is?

00:44:52.628 --> 00:44:55.255
Serious? You mean,
another thing I don't know about!

00:45:01.053 --> 00:45:02.971
Yeah, it's always been like this.

00:45:05.349 --> 00:45:07.059
You always had

00:45:08.685 --> 00:45:11.021
something serious going on
that I didn't know about.

00:45:11.104 --> 00:45:12.564
From the very start.

00:45:13.774 --> 00:45:17.861
Because you were writing
or because you had writer's block.

00:45:21.990 --> 00:45:24.576
I was always here,
and yet you never cared about me.

00:45:25.911 --> 00:45:26.954
Do you even know

00:45:27.955 --> 00:45:31.166
how shitty I feel
whenever I do couples counseling?

00:45:31.667 --> 00:45:34.586
"Talk to each other constantly.
Communication is key."

00:45:36.338 --> 00:45:38.048
That's what I tell them, yet I…

00:45:40.801 --> 00:45:41.718
We…

00:45:44.596 --> 00:45:47.099
You're the one who doesn't know a thing.

00:45:48.725 --> 00:45:51.353
How much I let slide.

00:45:51.436 --> 00:45:56.108
How long I've put up with you,

00:45:57.568 --> 00:45:58.986
waited for you,

00:46:00.487 --> 00:46:02.072
and endured you.

00:46:04.408 --> 00:46:05.659
Do you have any idea?

00:46:09.746 --> 00:46:11.415
Quit your whining.

00:48:03.735 --> 00:48:04.820
<i>A comb? Nice.</i>

00:48:04.903 --> 00:48:06.530
<i>So you're not empty-handed.</i>

00:48:06.613 --> 00:48:08.532
<i>-A comb.</i>
<i>-No one has their phone</i>…

00:48:20.127 --> 00:48:21.253
LEE KANG

00:48:30.303 --> 00:48:31.930
<i>The person you are calling</i>…

00:49:33.450 --> 00:49:34.367
What is it?

00:49:37.871 --> 00:49:39.331
Don't tell me that punk…

00:49:40.665 --> 00:49:41.875
At this hour?

00:49:54.471 --> 00:49:56.890
Mr. Heo, I know everything. Everything!

00:49:57.557 --> 00:49:59.601
-I know all of Mr. Kim's secrets--
-Quiet!

00:50:00.102 --> 00:50:00.936
Quickly, get in.

00:50:01.978 --> 00:50:03.480
I know everything. Really.

00:50:03.563 --> 00:50:05.190
Just get inside.

00:50:06.191 --> 00:50:07.150
Hurry.

00:50:16.493 --> 00:50:18.370
Have you totally lost it?

00:50:18.870 --> 00:50:20.163
How come you…

00:50:20.664 --> 00:50:22.290
Why did you come here at this time?

00:50:22.374 --> 00:50:26.002
Do you know what's even more shocking?
Know what's even more riveting?

00:50:26.086 --> 00:50:27.629
You've seriously lost it.

00:50:27.712 --> 00:50:28.880
Mr. Heo, that young man

00:50:29.506 --> 00:50:31.091
wasn't Se-yun.

00:50:31.716 --> 00:50:33.468
It wasn't Se-yun!

00:50:44.646 --> 00:50:46.731
Se-yun! It's me, Lee Kang!

00:50:47.232 --> 00:50:48.650
Hey, stop!

00:51:10.255 --> 00:51:12.591
What? That young man…

00:51:14.384 --> 00:51:15.844
wasn't Kim Se-yun?

00:51:17.179 --> 00:51:18.513
No, it was Mrs. Ahn.

00:51:20.265 --> 00:51:21.683
Se-yun's mom.

00:51:22.434 --> 00:51:23.268
Ahn Eun-joo.

00:51:29.316 --> 00:51:30.400
Ahn Eun-joo?

00:51:54.049 --> 00:51:55.175
It was Eun-joo?

00:51:59.262 --> 00:52:00.764
It was dear Eun-joo?

00:52:04.226 --> 00:52:05.769
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:52:05.852 --> 00:52:07.187
<i>It was Eun-joo?</i>

